 â€¢ One pod per node by default
 â€¢ Uses node selectors, taints/tolerations, or affinity rules to limit scope
 â€¢ Compatible with static pods, but easier to manage via the Kubernetes API
 â€¢ Managed by the control planeâ€”no need for manual deployment when scaling the cluster

