 â€¢ DaemonSets are not ideal for workloads that need horizontal scalingâ€”use Deployments or StatefulSets for those.
 â€¢ Use resource requests and limits to avoid overloading your nodes.
 â€¢ Combine with RBAC if your DaemonSet needs access to node-level APIs or host paths.
 â€¢ Use tolerations if you need to run on tainted nodes (like control-plane nodes).

