 â€¢ Imagine you're running a Kubernetes cluster with multiple nodes and want to collect logs from each.
 â€¢ You can deploy Fluentd or Filebeat as a DaemonSet, and it will automatically spin up a pod on every nodeâ€”collecting and shipping logs without manual intervention.

The same concept applies to monitoring metrics, running network overlays, or even syncing files across nodes.

